"\n\nPepper is a social humanoid robot designed to interact with humans. It was created by SoftBank Robotics (formerly known as Aldebaran Robotics) and launched in 2014. Pepper was designed to be sociable and communicate with people through voice and touch. It can recognize faces, answer questions, and even help with e-commerce tasks. It can be programmed to do everything from providing customer service to helping with household tasks like setting the thermostat. Pepper also receives updates from time to time, allowing it to develop its skills over time."